-- Heinz Weighs Almost 250 Job Cuts in U.K., Ireland
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2013-08-21T15:38:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-21/heinz-weighs-almost-250-job-cuts-in-u-k-ireland.html
HJ Heinz Co., the ketchup maker
taken private this year by Warren Buffett’s  Berkshire Hathaway
Inc. (BRK/A)  and Jorge Paulo Lemann’s 3G Capital, said its weighing job
cuts in the U.K. and Ireland.  “Heinz continues to examine every aspect of our business
globally to ensure we are operating as efficiently and
effectively as possible in order to reach our growth goals,”
Michael Mullen, a spokesman for Pittsburgh-based Heinz wrote in
an e-mailed statement. Proposals “may result in the elimination
of 248 office positions across the U.K. and Ireland. We regret
the impact this may have.”  SkyNews previously reported on the potential job cuts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in  New York  at 
